## Verification Checklist

- [ ] `handleWebhook()` has a complete `case "pull_request"` implementation
- [ ] PR `opened` action creates a deployment record with `type='preview'`, `status='queued'`, `pr_number` set
- [ ] PR `synchronize` action creates a new deployment record (same fields as opened)
- [ ] PR `reopened` action creates a new deployment record (same fields as opened)
- [ ] PR `closed` action looks up active preview and triggers cleanup
- [ ] PR `closed` with no active preview logs and returns without error
- [ ] Unknown PR actions (e.g., `labeled`, `assigned`) are logged at debug level and ignored
- [ ] Project lookup by `installationId` + `repoFullName` works
- [ ] Missing project logs a warning and returns (no error thrown)
- [ ] Duplicate delivery/commit is detected and skipped
- [ ] Async build dispatch does not block the webhook response
- [ ] All errors are caught and logged (webhook always returns 200)

